    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix Msg3 scheduling for missing TDD configurations in eNB scheduler\n\n### Summary\nThe `get_Msg3alloc()` function in the eNB scheduler was not properly handling all TDD subframe configurations, causing unexpected behavior during RACH procedures. When the eNB was configured with TDD configurations 0, 2, or 6, or when certain subframes were used for RAR transmission, the function would leave the output parameters `*frame` and `*subframe` uninitialized, leading to incorrect Msg3 scheduling.\n\nThis issue manifested as UEs failing to transmit Msg3 within the expected timing window, causing RACH failures and connection establishment timeouts. The problem was particularly evident in TDD mode where specific subframe assignments weren't handled by the existing implementation.\n\nThe root cause was incomplete switch statements that only covered a subset of possible subframe values, and missing handling for TDD subframe assignments 0, 2, and 6 entirely.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler_primitives.c`: \n  * Added complete handling for all TDD subframe assignments (0-6)\n  * Added default cases to all switch statements to ensure output parameters are always initialized\n  * Implemented proper fallback behavior using FDD-like timing (subframe + 6 with wraparound)\n  * Added clear comments documenting each TDD configuration pattern\n"
}